      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "In order to remain in good standing in this program and be recommended for teacher licensure, candidates are required to maintain a cumulative grade-point average of 2.5 (A= 4.0)."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Departmental distinction: Students should consult their advisers by the second semester of the junior year for information pertaining to seminar honors work and honors awards in the department."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "The total of 47 hours may be reduced by as much as 16 hours through prerequisite credit for work equivalent to GER 101-GER 104 taken in secondary school.",
